title:
Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL) Shares Sold by Dixon Mitchell Investment 
Counsel Inc.
text: Posted by Defense World Staff on Mar 29th, 2024 Dixon Mitchell Investment Counsel Inc. cut its stake in  Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ:GOOGL – Free Report) by 0.8% in the fourth quarter, according to the company in its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  owned 748,334 shares of the information services provider’s stock after selling 5,912 shares during the period. Alphabet comprises approximately  5.6% of Dixon Mitchell Investment Counsel Inc.’s holdings, making the stock its 2nd largest holding. Dixon Mitchell Investment Counsel Inc.’s holdings in Alphabet were worth $104,535,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently bought and sold shares of the company. Finally, Norges Bank bought a new stake in  Alphabet during the fourth quarter worth about $8,335,063,000. 40.03% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds.
